="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#989dca><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bthecrossroadstavern8833.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=banewolf>Banewolf</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>22</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>4/12/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>10:17:33 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">SOTS, KEG, Public - Community effort. Need input </font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Well would like to throw out some ideas and viewpoints. On ECI the public was a very large organization. The seemed to take precedence over the large guilds. This was one of the factors that caused lots of “problems” with feeling towards SOTS (I use them as an example because they were at the root of many complains on ECI). You know what SOTS, KEG, etc.. All have the same rights as everyone else on the server. They pay just like the rest of us to play. They shouldn’t have to miss out of Raids, events, etc just because the “Public” feels they have the right, we are all equal. We all pay, we all devote time to the game.  What I have noticed so far is the large and powerful guilds seem to be working out schedules VERY well. I could be wrong on this but that is the impression I have. The Public I think needs a representative, someone who can work out schedules with the guilds of Zeb.  I don’t think there should be the rotating schedules like there was on ECI, i.e. Public had Hate Mon, Tues, Sat, and Sun… This representative could be someone who is guildless or a member of one of the large guilds doesn’t matter as long as they can work with other guilds on scheduling.  This is in the best interest of the Public. I believe SOT’s moved to the new server because of all the political crap that had to deal with on ECI, not sure about the guilds that moved from Rathe but might be similar reasons. The Public is not going to be able to assemble a bunch of people, head to Hate or Fear zone in and them complain because a large guild is there.  I for one have no sympathy for situation like this.  Again they have the same right as everyone else, if they worked out something with the other guilds and found no problems with doing that then they can / should be able to. Without a representative for the Public not only will you have a hard time getting Raids but might end up at the other end of the whacking stick and enraging the large guild by disturbing their plans. I for one do enjoy Public Raids. Being only 53 I can’t participate with some of the guilds on Zeb due to lvl restrictions. But enjoy meeting new people and making new friends. I would like to hear of others thoughts and ideas on this</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#dcdeed><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udivinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Divinia</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Loud Mouthed Wench</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>21</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>4/12/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>10:28:11 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.nexus2.f2s.com/StandardSmall.jpg width=178 height=134></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: SOTS, KEG, Public - Community effort. Need input </font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I agree with much of this. When I came to this server my guild broke up at the last minute. So here I am at level 52, considering guilds I'd like to join; unfortunatly 95% of the large guilds have level restrictions even on joining that would exclude me. So essentially if I'd like to go on a raid (something needs to break the monotony of leveling), I either need an invite by a guild or go on a public raid.<br>
<br>
The deal is that large guilds are organized in a serious way. I've been on Raids with KEG, CIW, and other large guilds and am impressed with what they accomplish. I've shown up for public raids and found them to be chaotic and most of the time never even start due to lack of interest.<br>
<br>
So where does that leave me? I've spent 2 year on this character to be able to go on these wonderful adventures called raids but now I find myself severly limited.<br>
<br>
As I have said on another post on this board; we need to find a system that will give everyone opportunity. We have a chance for a new start here and to create a server society that has a different mindset other than the "me first" attitude that seems to pervade other servers.<br>
<br>
I don't have any answers myself but this discussion is a great start!<br>
</font><P><center>
