<br>
Guild raids tend to be well organised because everyone knows what they're doing and what they have to do. On the other hand public raids contain a high proportion of people that don't know what they're doing and a proportion of those are not willing to find out what they should be doing.<br>
<br>
But it's unfair to tar all us pubbies with the same brush. some of us do what we do very well, and even if we don't know what's going on we're willing to ask and listen if need be.<br>
<br>
As for a representative... if the Guilds represent the corporations of the world, then yes, we could do with a president to represent the public. Just don't mention the word &quot;calendar&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
On E'ci we had various Guilded people that were willing to share their experiences with the public and lead raids.<br>
<br>
Or maybe we could have a &quot;For hire&quot; section, whereby a Guild going on a raid can &quot;hire&quot; the Guildless for a raid to fill missing spots maybe with the intention of recruiting?<br>
<br>
It is hard though, a lot of the major Guilds are as full as they want to be and getting in, even if you're of the required level for the Guild, is rather difficult.<br>
<br>
But yes, it is difficult for those of us in smaller Guilds or Guildless, and I think it would be a shame if I'd have to join a large Guild if I wanted a chance to raid. I like my individuality and I'd rather not just been seen as 1 in a pool of Shaman.<br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#989dca><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ujerrica.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jerrica</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Pantless Wonder of KEG</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>9</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>4/12/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>11:32:56 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.attrition.org/eq/sigs/jerrica.gif height=178 width=165></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: SOTS, KEG, Public - Community effort. Need input </font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">*Repost from Poll board*<br>
<br>
From my perspective, it's not a matter of people fearing change. The Rathe guilds have been there, and know exactly what to expect. We have a very informed opinion on how a Calendar works, and how it eventually can turn out. As we lived with one for well over a year. Do you have the same experience from Eci? <br>
<br>
Personally I don't want to know 3 weeks ahead of time that I will be in a place anymore. I like logging in and having an actual *choice* of things to do for a change. This is such a refreshing change for the Rathe guilds. Where we had one plane a month if we were lucky, Trakanon on a rotation that turned into 6 guilds and one Trak every few weeks.<br>
<br>
I was one of the biggest supporters of the Rathe calendar almost up until the end when I saw just how ugly it had become. I helped get the rules off the ground with members of CIW and Bots. It turned very ugly, even if you threw out the Epic stuff, there was still enough ugliness left.<br>
<br>
I'm pretty sure you'll only see some of the main guilds in Fear/Hate on patch days when the Gods are up. That leaves probably 25ish days that the planes are free. Take the initiative and do /who all druid for Fear or /who all cleric for Hate to see if anybody is up there  <br>
<br>
Plane of Growth, my guild hasnt gone there in god knows how long. Not sure I've see many of the other high end game guilds in there either. That's a heck of a lot of open plane days for the people worried about a Calendar. And if you are interested in the high end Velious spawns, get your troops organized and there and *beat* the other guilds to them. My guild has about 8-9 options now when it comes to Patch days and the couple days following, if all else fails we can head to ToV and get some armour to make up for any "lost" opportunities.<br>
<br>
As for the high end game, there is no rotation or "Calendar" other than informal heads up communication between the guilds.<br>
<br>
If your problem is Trakanon or VS, talk to the guilds who are actually killing them now. There are only a handful killing them on a regular basis from what I see.<br>
<br>
Do a /who all count sometime on Zeb, when there was 1700 people online at peak time last night, 1200 of those were lvl 50 and under. I don't foresee a huge overcrowding problem on this server for a very very long time.<br>
