<br>
1.  We hear patch is scheduled.  Someone posts it on our board.  People read this and know they'll be busy that day.<br>
<br>
2.  We discuss what we want to go for.  We take into account what we believe we are capable of, what other guilds are likely to go for, and our needs.<br>
<br>
3.  One of our guild leaders/officers says: &quot;we go for this&quot;.  And maybe he'll throw out an alternate target or two.<br>
<br>
4.  We get on-line.  We head to our destination.  If it's busy, we go else where.<br>
<br>
